title: No. 21 Cowboys survive West Virginia's rally, win in overtime
text:
No. 21 Cowboys survive West Virginia's rally, win in overtime Published 10:15 PM CDT Oct 10, 2015 A Large Text Photos 
The No. 21 Cowboys survived the Mountaineers' rally in the second half, beating West Virginia 33-26 in overtime Saturday in Morgantown. Related Saturday starts off cold for Oklahoma... 
West Virginia (4-1) scored 24 points in the second half and held Oklahoma State (5-1) to six points in the third quarter and three points in the fourth. The Cowboys botched an extra point in the third quarter. 
The Cowboys scored on the first possession of overtime on a 2-yard run on 4th and 1 by J.W. Walsh, and the defense held to seal the victory.
